<li id="cite_note-VulgarisAerae1-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-VulgarisAerae1_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-VulgarisAerae1_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://worldcat.org/wcpa/oclc/62188677" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/wcpa/oclc/62188677" rel="nofollow">"Earliest-found use of "vulgaris aerae" (Latin for Common Era) (1615)"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://worldcat.org/wcpa/oclc/62188677" class="external free" title="http://worldcat.org/wcpa/oclc/62188677" rel="nofollow">http://worldcat.org/wcpa/oclc/62188677</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-01-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Earliest-found+use+of+%22vulgaris+aerae%22+%28Latin+for+Common+Era%29+%281615%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fworldcat.org%2Fwcpa%2Foclc%2F62188677&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BJohannes_Kepler.5D.5D1615"><a href="/wiki/Johannes_Kepler" title="Johannes Kepler">Johannes Kepler</a> (1615) (in Latin). <i>Joannis Keppleri Eclogae chronicae: ex epistolis doctissimorum aliquot virorum &amp; suis mutuis, quibus examinantur tempora nobilissima: 1. Herodis Herodiadumque, 2. baptismi &amp; ministerii Christi annorum non plus 2 1/4, 3. passionis, mortis et resurrectionis Dn. N. Iesu Christi, anno aerae nostrae vulgaris 31. non, ut vulgo 33., 4. belli Iudaici, quo funerata fuit cum Ierosolymis &amp; Templo Synagoga Iudaica, sublatumque Vetus Testamentum. Inter alia &amp; commentarius in locum Epiphanii obscurissimum de cyclo veteri Iudaeorum.</i>. Francofurti&#160;: Tampach.  "anno aerae nostrae vulgaris"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joannis+Keppleri+Eclogae+chronicae%3A+ex+epistolis+doctissimorum+aliquot+virorum+%26+suis+mutuis%2C+quibus+examinantur+tempora+nobilissima%3A+1.+Herodis+Herodiadumque%2C+2.+baptismi+%26+ministerii+Christi+annorum+non+plus+2+1%2F4%2C+3.+passionis%2C+mortis+et+resurrectionis+Dn.+N.+Iesu+Christi%2C+anno+aerae+nostrae+vulgaris+31.+non%2C+ut+vulgo+33.%2C+4.+belli+Iudaici%2C+quo+funerata+fuit+cum+Ierosolymis+%26+Templo+Synagoga+Iudaica%2C+sublatumque+Vetus+Testamentum.+Inter+alia+%26+commentarius+in+locum+Epiphanii+obscurissimum+de+cyclo+veteri+Iudaeorum.&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BJohannes+Kepler%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BJohannes+Kepler%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1615&amp;rft.pub=Francofurti+%3A+Tampach&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Irvin-6">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Irvin_6-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Irvin_6-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=C2akvQfa-QMC&amp;pg=PR11&amp;dq=before+%22common+era%22+christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=J5x3M_bx6EXYYxL57m08w5OYzWk" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=C2akvQfa-QMC&amp;pg=PR11&amp;dq=before+%22common+era%22+christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=J5x3M_bx6EXYYxL57m08w5OYzWk" rel="nofollow">"History of the World Christian Movement"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=C2akvQfa-QMC&amp;pg=PR11&amp;dq=before+%22common+era%22+christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=J5x3M_bx6EXYYxL57m08w5OYzWk" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=C2akvQfa-QMC&amp;pg=PR11&amp;dq=before+%22common+era%22+christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=J5x3M_bx6EXYYxL57m08w5OYzWk" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=C2akvQfa-QMC&amp;pg=PR11&amp;dq=before+%22common+era%22+christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=J5x3M_bx6EXYYxL57m08w5OYzWk</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-01-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+World+Christian+Movement&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DC2akvQfa-QMC%26pg%3DPR11%26dq%3Dbefore%2B%2522common%2Bera%2522%2Bchristian%26lr%3D%26sig%3DJ5x3M_bx6EXYYxL57m08w5OYzWk&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFIrvinSunquist.2C_Scott2001">Irvin, Dale T.; Sunquist, Scott (2001). <i>History of the World Christian Movement</i>. Continuum International Publishing Group. pp.&#160;xi. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0567088669" class="internal">ISBN 0567088669</a>.  "The influence of western culture and scholarship upon the rest of the world in turn led to this system of dating becoming the most widely used one across the globe today. Many scholars in historical and religious studies in the West in recent years have sought to lessen the explicitly Christian meaning of this system without abandoning the usefulness of a single, common, global form of dating. For this reason the terms <i>common era</i> and <i>before the common era</i>, abbreviated as CE and BCE, have grown in popularity as designations. The terms are meant, in deference to non-Christians, to soften the explicit theological claims made by the older Latin terminology, while at the same time providing continuity with earlier generations of mostly western Christian historical research."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+World+Christian+Movement&amp;rft.aulast=Irvin&amp;rft.aufirst=Dale+T.&amp;rft.au=Irvin%2C+Dale+T.&amp;rft.au=Sunquist%2C+Scott&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3Bxi&amp;rft.pub=Continuum+International+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.isbn=0567088669&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=-VLt0uQrzXMC&amp;pg=PA18&amp;dq=before+common+era+christian+non-christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=rl3B9VZmkG8RtbP6WZifd9iCJ2A" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=-VLt0uQrzXMC&amp;pg=PA18&amp;dq=before+common+era+christian+non-christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=rl3B9VZmkG8RtbP6WZifd9iCJ2A" rel="nofollow">"Get Set for Religious Studies"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=-VLt0uQrzXMC&amp;pg=PA18&amp;dq=before+common+era+christian+non-christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=rl3B9VZmkG8RtbP6WZifd9iCJ2A" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=-VLt0uQrzXMC&amp;pg=PA18&amp;dq=before+common+era+christian+non-christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=rl3B9VZmkG8RtbP6WZifd9iCJ2A" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=-VLt0uQrzXMC&amp;pg=PA18&amp;dq=before+common+era+christian+non-christian&amp;lr=&amp;sig=rl3B9VZmkG8RtbP6WZifd9iCJ2A</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-01-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Get+Set+for+Religious+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D-VLt0uQrzXMC%26pg%3DPA18%26dq%3Dbefore%2Bcommon%2Bera%2Bchristian%2Bnon-christian%26lr%3D%26sig%3Drl3B9VZmkG8RtbP6WZifd9iCJ2A&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCorrywrightMorgan.2C_Peggy2006">Corrywright, Dominic; Morgan, Peggy (2006). <i>Get Set for Religious Studies</i>. Edinburgh University Press. pp.&#160;18. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/074862032X" class="internal">ISBN 074862032X</a>.  "Also note where AD (from the Latin 'in the year of our Lord') and BC (before Christ) are used in datings, for although the numerical calculation of this system is now the international convention, the terminology used in religious studies is CE (common era) and BCE (before the common era), which are more neutrally descriptive terms"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Get+Set+for+Religious+Studies&amp;rft.aulast=Corrywright&amp;rft.aufirst=Dominic&amp;rft.au=Corrywright%2C+Dominic&amp;rft.au=Morgan%2C+Peggy&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B18&amp;rft.pub=Edinburgh+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=074862032X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-cst-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-cst_8-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFAndrew_Herrmann2006">Andrew Herrmann (2006-05-27). <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20071012132841/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20071012132841/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633" rel="nofollow">"BCE date designation called more sensitive"</a>. Chicago Sun-Times. Archived from <a href="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633" class="external text" title="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633" rel="nofollow">the original</a> on 2008-10-03<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20071012132841/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633" class="external free" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20071012132841/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633" rel="nofollow">http://web.archive.org/web/20071012132841/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4155/is_20060527/ai_n16436633</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-06-15</span>.  "Herrmann observes, "The changes — showing up at museums, in academic circles and in school textbooks — have been touted as more sensitive to people of faiths outside of Christianity." However, Herrmann notes, "The use of BCE and CE have rankled some Christians"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=BCE+date+designation+called+more+sensitive&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Andrew+Herrmann&amp;rft.au=Andrew+Herrmann&amp;rft.date=2006-05-27&amp;rft.pub=Chicago+Sun-Times&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20071012132841%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Ffindarticles.com%2Fp%2Farticles%2Fmi_qn4155%2Fis_20060527%2Fai_n16436633&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <i>Anno Domini</i> (which means <i>in the year of the/our Lord</i>)<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><a href="http://www.m-w.com/dictionary/Anno%20Domini" class="external text" title="http://www.m-w.com/dictionary/Anno%20Domini" rel="nofollow">"Anno Domini"</a>. <i>Merriam Webster Online Dictionary</i>. Merriam-Webster. 2003<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.m-w.com/dictionary/Anno%20Domini" class="external free" title="http://www.m-w.com/dictionary/Anno%20Domini" rel="nofollow">http://www.m-w.com/dictionary/Anno%20Domini</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-02-04</span>.  "Etymology: Medieval Latin, in the year of the Lord".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Anno+Domini&amp;rft.atitle=Merriam+Webster+Online+Dictionary&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Merriam-Webster&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.m-w.com%2Fdictionary%2FAnno%2520Domini&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Translated as "in the year of (Our) Lord" in Blackburn, B &amp; Holford-Strevens, L, (2003), <i>The Oxford Companion to the Year</i>, Oxford University Press, 782.</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.religioustolerance.org/ce_info1.htm#wce" class="external text" title="http://www.religioustolerance.org/ce_info1.htm#wce" rel="nofollow">"Historical background of the use of "CE" and "BCE" to identify dates"</a>. Ontario Consultants on Religious Tolerance<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.religioustolerance.org/ce_info1.htm#wce" class="external free" title="http://www.religioustolerance.org/ce_info1.htm#wce" rel="nofollow">http://www.religioustolerance.org/ce_info1.htm#wce</a></span>.  "According to David Barrett et al, editors of the "World Christian Encyclopedia: A comparative survey of churches and religions - AD 30 to 2200," there are 19 major world religions which are subdivided into a total of 270 large religious groups, and many smaller ones. The vast majority do not recognize Yeshua of Nazareth as either God or Messiah. Expecting followers of other religions to imply this status for Yeshua can create ill feeling."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Historical+background+of+the+use+of+%22CE%22+and+%22BCE%22+to+identify+dates&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Ontario+Consultants+on+Religious+Tolerance&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.religioustolerance.org%2Fce_info1.htm%23wce&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFHeustis2007">Heustis, Reer R, Jr. (2007-09-09). <a href="http://www.renewamerica.us/columns/heustis/070909" class="external text" title="http://www.renewamerica.us/columns/heustis/070909" rel="nofollow">"Common Era and the culture war"</a>. RenewAmerica<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.renewamerica.us/columns/heustis/070909" class="external free" title="http://www.renewamerica.us/columns/heustis/070909" rel="nofollow">http://www.renewamerica.us/columns/heustis/070909</a></span>.  "referred to as <i>Year of our Lord</i>, which is an unmistakable reference to the Lord Jesus Christ....Not every person believes that Jesus is the Lord, they argue, and therefore, he should not have to acknowledge Christ's <i>Lordship</i>...Make no mistake about it: Jesus Christ is not only the Lord of Christians — He is also the Lord of all."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Common+Era+and+the+culture+war&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Heustis&amp;rft.aufirst=Reer+R%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.au=Heustis%2C+Reer+R%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.date=2007-09-09&amp;rft.pub=RenewAmerica&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.renewamerica.us%2Fcolumns%2Fheustis%2F070909&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Wilson-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Wilson_12-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFWilson.2C_Kenneth_G.1993">Wilson, Kenneth G. (1993). <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/68/20/120.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bartleby.com/68/20/120.html" rel="nofollow">"The Columbia Guide to Standard American English – A.D., B.C., (A.)C.E., B.C.E."</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/68/20/120.html" class="external free" title="http://www.bartleby.com/68/20/120.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.bartleby.com/68/20/120.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-06-16</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Columbia+Guide+to+Standard+American+English+%E2%80%93+A.D.%2C+B.C.%2C+%28A.%29C.E.%2C+B.C.E.&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Wilson%2C+Kenneth+G.&amp;rft.au=Wilson%2C+Kenneth+G.&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bartleby.com%2F68%2F20%2F120.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.chicagomanualofstyle.org/about15_rules.html" class="external text" title="http://www.chicagomanualofstyle.org/about15_rules.html" rel="nofollow">"Major Rule Changes in The Chicago Manual of Style, Fifteenth Edition"</a>. University of Chicago Press. <i>15th ed.:</i> 2003<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.chicagomanualofstyle.org/about15_rules.html" class="external free" title="http://www.chicagomanualofstyle.org/about15_rules.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.chicagomanualofstyle.org/about15_rules.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-09-12</span>.  "Certain abbreviations traditionally set in small caps are now in full caps (AD, BCE, and the like), with small caps an option."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Major+Rule+Changes+in+The+Chicago+Manual+of+Style%2C+Fifteenth+Edition&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=%27%2715th+ed.%3A%27%27+2003&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagomanualofstyle.org%2Fabout15_rules.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Pedersen-14">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Pedersen_14-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Pedersen_14-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Pedersen, O., (1983), "The Ecclesiastical Calendar and the Life of the Church" in Coyne, G.V. et al. (Eds.) <a href="http://articles.adsabs.harvard.edu//full/book/grc../1983//0000001,001.html" class="external text" title="http://articles.adsabs.harvard.edu//full/book/grc../1983//0000001,001.html" rel="nofollow"><i>The Gregorian Reform of the Calendar</i></a>, Vatican Observatory, p. 50.</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> Doggett, L.E., (1992), <a href="http://charon.nmsu.edu/~lhuber/leaphist.html" class="external text" title="http://charon.nmsu.edu/~lhuber/leaphist.html" rel="nofollow">"Calendars"</a> in Seidelmann, P.K., <i>The Explanatory Supplement to the Astronomical Almanac</i>, Sausalito CA: University Science Books, p. 579.</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBromiley1995">Bromiley, Geoffrey W. (1995). <i><a href="http://books.google.ca/books?id=BW_1mt4oebQC&amp;pg=PA686&amp;dq=jesus+birth+year+before" class="external text" title="http://books.google.ca/books?id=BW_1mt4oebQC&amp;pg=PA686&amp;dq=jesus+birth+year+before" rel="nofollow">The International Standard Bible Encyclopedia</a></i>. Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0802837816" class="internal">ISBN 0802837816</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.ca/books?id=BW_1mt4oebQC&amp;pg=PA686&amp;dq=jesus+birth+year+before" class="external free" title="http://books.google.ca/books?id=BW_1mt4oebQC&amp;pg=PA686&amp;dq=jesus+birth+year+before" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.ca/books?id=BW_1mt4oebQC&amp;pg=PA686&amp;dq=jesus+birth+year+before</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-12-25</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+International+Standard+Bible+Encyclopedia&amp;rft.aulast=Bromiley&amp;rft.aufirst=Geoffrey+W.&amp;rft.au=Bromiley%2C+Geoffrey+W.&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=Wm.+B.+Eerdmans+Publishing&amp;rft.isbn=0802837816&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.ca%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBW_1mt4oebQC%26pg%3DPA686%26dq%3Djesus%2Bbirth%2Byear%2Bbefore&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
