<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=nK6IPj-Wk-kC&amp;pg=PA10&amp;dq=%22vulgar+era+of+the+NATIVITY%22" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=nK6IPj-Wk-kC&amp;pg=PA10&amp;dq=%22vulgar+era+of+the+NATIVITY%22" rel="nofollow">""vulgar era of the nativity" (1796)"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=nK6IPj-Wk-kC&amp;pg=PA10&amp;dq=%22vulgar+era+of+the+NATIVITY%22" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=nK6IPj-Wk-kC&amp;pg=PA10&amp;dq=%22vulgar+era+of+the+NATIVITY%22" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=nK6IPj-Wk-kC&amp;pg=PA10&amp;dq=%22vulgar+era+of+the+NATIVITY%22</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%22vulgar+era+of+the+nativity%22+%281796%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DnK6IPj-Wk-kC%26pg%3DPA10%26dq%3D%2522vulgar%2Bera%2Bof%2Bthe%2BNATIVITY%2522&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRev._Robert_Walker.2C_Isaac_Newton.2C_Thomas_Falconer">Rev. Robert Walker, Isaac Newton, Thomas Falconer. <i>Analysis of Researches Into the Origin and Progress of Historical Time, from the Creation to ...</i>. London: T. Cadell Jr. and W. Davies. pp.&#160;p10.  "Dionysius the Little brought the vulgar era of the nativity too low by four years."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Analysis+of+Researches+Into+the+Origin+and+Progress+of+Historical+Time%2C+from+the+Creation+to+...&amp;rft.aulast=Rev.+Robert+Walker%2C+Isaac+Newton%2C+Thomas+Falcon