<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=qDaKGAAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22christian+era%22" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=qDaKGAAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22christian+era%22" rel="nofollow">"first appearance of "Christian Era" in English (1652)"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=qDaKGAAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22christian+era%22" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=qDaKGAAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22christian+era%22" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=qDaKGAAACAAJ&amp;dq=%22christian+era%22</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-19</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=first+appearance+of+%22Christian+Era%22+in+English+%281652%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DqDaKGAAACAAJ%26dq%3D%2522christian%2Bera%2522&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSliter.2C_Robert1652">Sliter, Robert (1652). <i>A celestiall glasse, or, Ephemeris for the year of the Christian era 1652 being the bissextile or leap-year: contayning the lunations, planetary motions, configurations &amp; ecclipses for this present year ...&#160;: with many other things very delightfull and necessary for most sorts of men: calculated exactly and composed for ... Rochester</i>. London: Printed for the Company of Stationers.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+celestiall+glasse%2C+or%2C+Ephemeris+for+the+year+of+the+Christian+era+1652+being+the+bissextile+or+leap-year%3A+contayning+the+lunations%2C+planetary+motions%2C+configurations+%26+ecclipses+for+this+present+year+...+%3A+with+many+other+things+very+delightfull+and+necessary+for+most+sorts+of+men%3A+calculated+exactly+and+composed+for+...+Rochester&amp;rft.aulast=Sliter%2C+Robert&amp;rft.au=Sliter%2C+Robert&amp;rft.date=1652&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Printed+for+the+Company+of+Stationers&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=ze8ehe65hwcC&amp;pg=RA2-PA252&amp;dq=%22Common+Era%22+%22before+chrift%22++chriftian+common+era" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=ze8ehe65hwcC&amp;pg=RA2-PA252&amp;dq=%22Common+Era%22+%22before+chrift%22++chriftian+common+era" rel="nofollow">"first so-far-found use of <i>common era</i> in English (1715)"</a>. p252<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=ze8ehe65hwcC&amp;pg=RA2-PA252&amp;dq=%22Common+Era%22+%22before+chrift%22++chriftian+common+era" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=ze8ehe65hwcC&amp;pg=RA2-PA252&amp;dq=%22Common+Era%22+%22before+chrift%22++chriftian+common+era" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=ze8ehe65hwcC&amp;pg=RA2-PA252&amp;dq=%22Common+Era%22+%22before+chrift%22++chriftian+common+era</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-01-05</span>.  "Some say the World was created 3950 Years before the common Æra of Christ"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=first+so-far-found+use+of+%27%27common+era%27%27+in+English+%281715%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pages=p252&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dze8ehe65hwcC%26pg%3DRA2-PA252%26dq%3D%2522Common%2BEra%2522%2B%2522before%2Bchrift%2522%2B%2Bchriftian%2Bcommon%2Bera&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGregoryJohn_Nicholson.2C_John_Morphew1715">Gregory, David; John Nicholson, John Morphew (1715). <i>The Elements of Astronomy, Physical and Geometrical</i>. <b>v. 1</b>. London: printed for J. Nicholson, and sold by J. Morphew.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%