<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=tn0EAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=RA1-PA130&amp;dq=%22Common+aEra%22+%22chrift%22" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=tn0EAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=RA1-PA130&amp;dq=%22Common+aEra%22+%22chrift%22" rel="nofollow">"1759 use of common æra"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=tn0EAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=RA1-PA130&amp;dq=%22Common+aEra%22+%22chrift%22" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=tn0EAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=RA1-PA130&amp;dq=%22Common+aEra%22+%22chrift%22" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=tn0EAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=RA1-PA130&amp;dq=%22Common+aEra%22+%22chrift%22</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-01-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=1759+use+of+common+%C3%A6ra&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dtn0EAAAAYAAJ%26pg%3DRA1-PA130%26dq%3D%2522Common%2BaEra%2522%2B%2522chrift%2522&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSale1759">Sale, George (1759). <i>An Universal History: From the Earliest Accounts to the Present Time By George Sale,</i>. <b>v 13</b>. London: C. Bathurst [etc.]. pp.&#160;v 13, p 130.  "at which time they fixed that for their common era"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Universal+History%3A+From+the+Earliest+Accounts+to+the+Present+Time+By+George+Sale%2C&amp;rft.aulast=Sale&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft.au=Sale%2C+George&amp;rft.date=1759&amp;rft.volume=v+13&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3Bv+13%2C+p+130&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=C.+Bathurst+%