<li id="cite_note-43"><b><a href="#cite_ref-43" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=HKgMAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA711&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+incarnation%22" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=HKgMAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA711&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+incarnation%22" rel="nofollow">""common era of the Incarnation" (1833)"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=HKgMAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA711&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+incarnation%22" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=HKgMAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA711&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+incarnation%22" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=HKgMAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA711&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+incarnation%22</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-13</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%22common+era+of+the+Incarnation%22+%281833%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DHKgMAAAAYAAJ%26pg%3DPA711%26dq%3D%2522common%2Bera%2Bof%2Bthe%2Bincarnation%2522&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i>The Encyclopaedia Britannica: A Dictionary of Arts, Sciences, and General Literature</i>. <b>V</b> (9 ed.). New York: Henry G. Allen and Company. 1833. pp.&#160;9th edition, Vol V, p711.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Encyclopaedia+Britannica%3A+A+Dictionary+of+Arts%2C+Sciences%2C+and+General+Literature&amp;rft.date=1833&amp;rft.volume=V&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B9th+edition%2C+Vol+V%2C+p711&amp;rft.edition=9&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Henry+G.+Allen+and+Company&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=um44AAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+Nativity%22&amp;q=%22common+era%22+%22of+the+Nativity%22&amp;pgis=1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=um44AAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+Nativity%22&amp;q=%22common+era%22+%22of+the+Nativity%22&amp;pgis=1" rel="nofollow">""common era" "of the Nativity" (1864)"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=um44AAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+Nativity%22&amp;q=%22common+era%22+%22of+the+Nativity%22&amp;pgis=1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=um44AAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+Nativity%22&amp;q=%22common+era%22+%22of+the+Nativity%22&amp;pgis=1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=um44AAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=%22common+era+of+the+Nativity%22&amp;q=%22common+era%22+%22of+the+Nativity%22&amp;pgis=1</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-13</span>.  "It should be observed, however, that these years correspond to 492 and 493, a portion of the annals of Ulster being counted from the Incarnation, and being, therefore, one year before the common era of the Nativity of our Lord."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%22common+era%22+%22of+the+Nativity%22+%281864%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dum44AAAAMAAJ%26dq%3D%2522common%2Bera%2Bof%2Bthe%2BNativity%2522%26q%3D%2522common%2Bera%2522%2B%2522of%2Bthe%2BNativity%2522%26pgis%3D1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BJames_Henthorn_Todd.5D.5D1864"><a href="/wiki/James_Henthorn_Todd" title="James Henthorn Todd">James Henthorn Todd</a> (1864). 