<li id="cite_note-48"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/calendar.html#Years" class="external text" title="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/calendar.html#Years" rel="nofollow">"Jewish Calendar: Numbering of Jewish Years"</a>. Jewish Virtual Library<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/calendar.html#Years" class="external free" title="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/calendar.html#Years" rel="nofollow">http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/calendar.html#Years</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-09-02</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Jewish+Calendar%3A+Numbering+of+Jewish+Years&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Jewish+Virtual+Library&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jewishvirtuallibrary.org%2Fjsource%2FJudaism%2Fcalendar.html%23Years&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Gormley-49">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Gormley_49-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Gormley_49-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFMichael_Gormley">Michael Gormley (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2005-04-24"><a href="/wiki/April_24" title="April 24">24 April</a> <a href="/wiki/2005" title="2005">2005</a></span>). <a href="http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=2005_3864650" class="external text" title="http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=2005_3864650" rel="nofollow">"Use of B.C. and A.D. faces changing times"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Houston_Chronicle" title="Houston Chronicle">Houston Chronicle</a>. p.&#160;A–13<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=2005_3864650" class="external free" title="http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=2005_3864650" rel="nofollow">http://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=2005_3864650</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-08-30</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Use+of+B.C.+and+A.D.+faces+changing+times&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Michael+Gormley&amp;rft.au=Michael+Gormley&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B24+April%5D%5D+%5B%5B2005%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3BA%26ndash%3B13&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BHouston+Chronicle%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.chron.com%2FCDA%2Farchives%2Farchive.mpl%3Fid%3D2005_3864650&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (Registration required.)</li>
<li id="cite_note-50"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50" title="">^</a></b> See, for example, the Society for Historical Archaeology states in its more recent style guide "Do not use C.E. (current era) ... or B.C.E.; convert these expressions to A.D. and B.C." <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFSociety_for_Historical_Archaeology2006">Society for Historical Archaeology (December 2006). <a href="http://www.sha.org/publications/style_guide.htm#V-d" class="external text" title="http://www.sha.org/publications/style_guide.htm#V-d" rel="nofollow">"Style Guide"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sha.org/publications/style_guide.htm#V-d" class="external free" title="http://www.sha.org/publications/style_guide.htm#V-d" rel="nofollow">http://www.sha.org/publications/style_guide.htm#V-d</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-08-29</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Style+Guide&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Society+for+Historical+Archaeology&amp;rft.au=Society+for+Historical+Archaeology&amp;rft.date=December+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sha.org%2Fpublications%2Fstyle_guide.htm%23V-d&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>. Whereas the <a href="/wiki/American_Anthropological_Association" title="American Anthropological Association">American Anthropological Association</a> style guide <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFAmerican_Anthropological_Society2003">American Anthropological Society (January 2003). <a href="http://www.aaanet.org/pubs/style_guide.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.aaanet.org/pubs/style_guide.pdf" rel="nofollow">"AAA Style Guide"</a> (PDF)<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.aaanet.org/pubs/style_guide.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.aaanet.org/pubs/style_guide.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.aaanet.org/pubs/style_guide.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-09-09</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=AAA+Style+Guide&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=American+Anthropological+Society&amp;rft.au=American+Anthropological+Society&amp;rft.date=January+2003&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.aaanet.org%2Fpubs%2Fstyle_guide.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Common_Era"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> takes a different approach.</li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.google.co.uk/search?as_q=BCE&amp;hl=en&amp;num=100&amp;btnG=Google+Search&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;lr=&amp;as_ft=i&amp;as_filetype=&amp;as_qdr=all&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_dt=i&amp;as_sitesearch=watchtower.org%2F&amp;as_rights=&amp;safe=images" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.google.co.uk/search?as_q=BCE&amp;hl=en&amp;num=100&amp;btnG=Google+Search&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;lr=&amp;as_ft=i&amp;as_filetype=&amp;as_qdr=all&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_dt=i&amp;as_sitesearch=watchtower.org%2F&amp;as_rights=&amp;safe=images" rel="nofollow">[1]</a> <a href="http://www.google.co.uk/search?num=100&amp;hl=en&amp;as_qdr=all&amp;q=BC+site%3Awatchtower.org%2F&amp;meta=" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.google.co.uk/search?num=100&amp;hl=en&amp;as_qdr=all&amp;q=BC+site%3Awatchtower.org%2F&amp;meta=" rel="nofollow">[2]</a> Also see, for example, comment "In this publication, instead of the traditional 'AD' and 'BC', the more accurate 'CE' (Common Era) and 'BCE' (before the Common Era) are used." in <i>The Bible — God's Word or Man's?</i>, p. 16 footnote, published by the Watchtower Bible and Tract Society of New York, Inc.</li>
